      skos:broader narr:PositioningThesis ;
      skos:prefLabel "Experts as Sources, Not Bottlenecks: Reach Expansion" ;
      skos:note "The product does not replace experts — it expands their reach exponentially while keeping their perspective traceable to them. The need for experts becomes the engine of the platform, not a problem to be solved. This reframes the 'What it replaces' section to 'What it changes.'" ;
      narr:theme "Experts are sources whose perspective scales exponentially through the platform — the need for experts is the engine, not the bottleneck" .

    # ── SECTION 6: Archetypes Restructured ───────────────────────────────────
    narr:Narrative_ArchetypeTaxonomyRestructured

      dct:source narr:Sample_StrategyDocV1_20260319 ;
      skos:broader narr:PersonasJTBD ;
      skos:prefLabel "Archetype Taxonomy: Whose Expertise × In What Context × Who Consumes" ;
      skos:note "Moved from four separate archetypes to a taxonomy structured by: whose expertise × in what context × who consumes it. Three archetypes: (1) The expert who distributes, (2) The leader who delegates, (3) The professional who works with AI daily. This supersedes the prior four-archetype model." ;
      narr:theme "Archetype taxonomy restructured from four separate types to a three-archetype matrix: whose expertise × context × consumer" .

