      skos:note "A role (head of marketing, clinical supervisor) is an abstraction that exists independently of the person filling it. The role has a module. It evolves over time. When someone new steps in, they install the role's module. This makes roles first-class product concepts, not just user categories." ;
      narr:theme "Organizational roles are abstractions with modules that persist independently of the person filling them — new occupants install the role" .

    # ── SECTION 8: Consulting Delivery as Module ─────────────────────────────
    narr:Claim_ConsultingDeliveryAsModule
